<br>
The planar armor turn ins are not cash cows. 8 or 9 hours up there, with a good 4 person group, steady kills, is only about 2.5k pp, including the gem drops and reward gems for handed in armor. In that same time, in level 64, you get about 15% of normal xp, and perhaps 35% AA, maybe 40. <br>
<br>
In droga, for example, every mob drops between 10 and 20 pp, you're looking at a better cash zone there, than hate. <br>
<br>
And the drops in hate, are all no-drop by and large where your ornate stuff would be a massive, massive payday.<br>
<br>
So sure, those who want to make 20k in a week of 8ish hour farms could do so; but I'd venture that anyone who is even lucky at an average rate, would win one 25k+ mold in BoT in a week of 8ish hour BoT camps, and get the xp to boot.<br>
<br>
Seer, if you can get past your penchance for the extreme examples you like to give, and actually put together multiple 40 person level 46+ guilds, then by all means, monopolize hate. You would need 5 additional guilds of 40 level 46+, in addition to your current guild/alliance and El'lar Dobluth to monopolize hate for one week. You'd need 26 additional guilds to do it for the entire month (One reserved day at a time, remember). If you can raise up 1040 people who want to screw with the calandar, HUZZAH and what not, more power to you. <br>
<br>
If you'd like to return to logical discussion, and cease trying to throw out strange and ineffectual examples to try to prove *me* wrong, that would be nice. <br>
<br>
