<br>
I'm sure you will continue to attempt some sort of 'yeah but' discussion, with little basis in reality and zero basis in facts, but I'll give you, again, the benefit of the doubt. <br>
<br>
They can ask for permission to keep farming spawns during a reserved raid until they are blue in the face, if the reserving guild says no, they have to leave, per the rules.<br>
<br>
If the reserving guild doesn't mind, what's your problem with that?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
As for rediculous examples that have nothing to do with the discussion, I think you beat me on that one with the scripted events thing. Now that has nothing to do with this disccusion at all.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Please also see the flame forum for my reply to this. <br>
<br>
However, here, I'll say that the apples and oranges argument that you are so fond of incorrectly using just bit you in the ass. <br>
<br>
Your panicked and utterly groundless claims of wild bands of FFA hate raiders is useless to the discussion. <br>
<br>
My systematic addressing of *any* and *all* reasons, hypothetical or otherwise, of why hate might be kept on a 24 hour reservation, followed up by saying why that statement does not fit, is a logical procedure to deny your argument. <br>
<br>
My 'exaggeration' and yours are beyond apples and oranges. It's rubber ducks and electrical tape. <br>
<br>
Sorry you can't see that, for whatever reason.<br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
<br>
